        <zone h='8594' id='8' type-v2='text' w='67789' x='146' y='391'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#005493' fontsize='18'>Business Impact Analysis — Delay Patterns by Segment &amp; Region </run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone forceUpdate='true' h='11979' id='9' type-v2='text' w='91581' x='732' y='86458'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000'>Operational Recommendations:</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000'>- Standard Class shipments account for the majority of delays. Review carrier capacity and routing efficiency for this shipping tier. </run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000'>- The Consumer segment experiences proportionally more delays than Corporate. Consider priority fulfillment adjustments for high-value consumer orders. </run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000'>- Using the ML prediction model to flag high-risk orders at time of placement allows logistics teams to reroute or escalate before delays occur, reducing operational cost and customer impact.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
      </zones>
